properties.Name: MasterContractType
properties.Description:
There are two types of master contracts - those that require member/employee contributions and those in which the employer or organization pays all premiums.

Ex:
CONTRIBUTORY
Members of employees pay contributions toward their insurance under the Master Contract relationship.

NON-CONTRIBUTORY
Employers or the sponsoring organization pay all premiums and fees toward their insurance of members under the Master Contract relationship.

Columns.Name: MasterContractTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Master Contract Type.

Columns.Name: MasterContractTypeName
Columns.Description: The name of the Master Contract Type.

Columns.Name: MasterContractTypeDescription
Columns.Description: The description of the Master Contract Type.
